In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugars and coffee granules. Gradually beat in flour and salt. On a lightly floured surface, roll out to 1/4-in. thickness. Cut with floured 2-in. to 3-in. cookie cutters. Place 2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 300 degrees F for 20-22 minutes or until set. Remove to wire racks to cool. Drizzle with melted chips.